unit.description: The acre is a unit of land area used in the imperial and US customary systems. It is traditionally defined as the area of one chain by one furlong (66 by 660 feet), which is exactly equal to 10 square chains, ​1⁄640 of a square mile, or 43,560 square feet, and approximately 4,047 m², or about 40% of a hectare.

model.description: This algorithm provides a fast method to summarize the univariate statistics for a regular grid over a polygonal region.  This algorithm returns equivalent results to existing methods, such as the raster stats python module or ESRI zonal statistics. This algorithm only counts a pixel if and only if the pixel centroid is located inside of the polygon.
